{
  "texts": [
    "top_k: changes how the model selects tokens for output.",
    "A top-K of 1 means the next token selected is the most probable among all tokens in the model's vocabulary (also called greedy decoding), while a top-K of 3 means the next token is chosen from the top three most probable tokens using temperature.",
    "At each token selection step, the top-K tokens with the highest probabilities are sampled.",
    "Then, tokens are filtered based on the top-P value, with the final token selected through temperature sampling.",
    "max_tokens: This is the maximum number of tokens that LLM generates in the response."
  ]
}